Recommendations
 Part 810 should establish new procedures, including binding time lines, for the review and approval of requests for specific authorizations, including expedited procedures for deemed exports.
 A provision to expedite the approval of specific authorizations for deemed exports with a binding deadline should be included. Since foreign government assurances are not required for “deemed export” authorizations, approval of these specific authorizations are completely within the control of
the U.S. government. Establishment of a binding deadline for processing these requests is consistent with Section 57.b(2) of the AEA.
